  "prompt": "What are the entry requirements for the University of Melbourne?",
  "response": "The University of Melbourne, located in Australia, has varying entry requirements depending on the program of study and the applicant's educational background. Here are some general entry requirements:\n\nFor undergraduate programs:\n- Completion of the Victorian Certificate of Education (VCE) or an equivalent qualification, with an Australian Tertitude Admission Rank (ATAR) score of at least 80-90, depending on the program.\n- English language proficiency, with a minimum International English Language Testing System (IELTS) score of 6.5 or equivalent.\n- Some programs may require specific prerequisite subjects, such as mathematics or science.\n\nFor postgraduate programs:\n- A relevant undergraduate degree from a recognized institution, with a minimum grade point average (GPA) of 65% or higher, depending on the program.\n- English language proficiency, with a minimum IELTS score of 6.5 or equivalent.\n- Some programs may require relevant work experience or additional qualifications.\n\nPlease note that meeting the minimum entry requirements does not guarantee admission, as the university receives a large number of applications and admission is competitive. It is always a good idea to check the specific entry requirements for your chosen program on the University of Melbourne's website.",
